Scribunto lualib (mw.html / mw.text / mw.uri + libraryUtil) — NOT vendored.

It is GPL-2.0-or-later, so it is no longer committed here. Instead it is fetched
at setup time by bin/scribuntounit-fetch into a local, gitignored cache
(<repoRoot>/.scribuntounit/lualib/) from:

  https://github.com/wikimedia/mediawiki-extensions-Scribunto
  path: includes/Engines/LuaCommon/lualib/

The ref to fetch is the consumer's choice — `scribunto.ref` in
scribuntounit.config.lua, overridable by the SCRIBUNTO_REF environment variable
(e.g. a CI matrix over REL1_43, REL1_44, …). The chosen ref IS the fidelity
guarantee: mw.html / mw.text / mw.uri behave as they do on a wiki running that
MediaWiki release. The runner reads the cache via paths.lualibRoot and never
redistributes the GPL code.
